#readme.dat

# constant.py -------------------------Defines Reynolds number, convergence tolerance, and mesh size
# mesh.py------------------------------Initializes the domain, control volume, and geometric spacing
# coefficients.py----------------------Computes convection-diffusion coefficients using the power-law scheme
# solver.py----------------------------Contains the core SIMPLE algorithm logic: momentum predictor, pressure corrector, and velocity correction
# plotting.py--------------------------Handles streamlines, pressure contour plots, and centerline extraction
# main.py------------------------------Orchestrates the simulation loop for Re = 100, 400, and 1000


# Instructions to run the code:
	#1. Open terminal
	#2. Go into the directory containing these Python scripts
	#3. Write in the command line: "python3 main.py"

# project_report---------contains the elaboration of the project
# project.pptx-----------contains the PowerPoint presentation described in the video

# Thank you!
